article.headline: Wright St. 61, Detroit 48
article.story: FAIRBORN, Ohio -- Todd Brown finished with 17 points and Wright State limited Detroit to only four points in the first 12 minutes on the way to a 61-48 victory on Saturday night. Will Graham added 10 points and six assists for the Raiders (16-10, 10-5 Horizon League), who never trailed. They built leads of as much as 25 points in the second half. Thomas Kennedy scored 14 points for Detroit (7-18, 2-13), which mustered just 15 points in the opening half. Down 32-15 at the break, the Titans never cut the lead to single digits in the final 20 minutes. They hit just 5-of-21 shots from the field in the first half (24 percent).
